Household InternationalInc said it expects its fully diluted earnings per share forthe first quarter to be about 35 pct above the same year-agoperiod.    It also looks for 1987 full-year fully diluted earnings tobe about 20 pct higher than the record 4.31 dlrs a sharereported for 1986.    Chairman Donald Clark, in remarks prepared for delivery toNew York security analysts, cited increased earnings fromHousehold Financial Services and "excellent return on equityfrom Household Manufacturing, combined with the impact of ourshare repurchase program, will result in higher earnings pershare and improved return on equity in 1987." Reuter&#3;